		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Negative feedback can lead to instability, if there's too much gain when phase lags by 180˚ (negative feedback becomes positive feedback at this point, and you know it's instable). So either reduce the amount of feedback, or stick in a small cap either at the input or output to further reduce gain at high-frequencies. But the fact that the output is buffered can indeed not help.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


